        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 4:28PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 428 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Ossining, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Ossining, Peekskill, Haverstraw, Mount Kisco, Mahopac, Lake Carmel,
Brewster, Carmel, Yorktown Heights, Stony Point, Jefferson Valley,
Putnam Valley, Croton-on-Hudson, Briarcliff Manor, and Buchanan.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
